  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Shelter and NFI Humanitarian Assistance for Displaced Populations in the Regions of Diffa, Maradi, and Tillab&#xE9;ry in Niger</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project allows IOM, as co-lead of the Shelter and NFI Working Group which is directed by the Ministry of Humanitarian Action and Disaster Management, to provide emergency humanitarian assistance to 4,000 households, or 28,000 most vulnerable displaced persons in the regions of Diffa, Maradi, and Tillab&#xE9;ri in Niger. This assistance through shelter and non-food item (NFI) support enables IOM to mitigate protection risks for affected populations and reduce their condition of instability.</narrative>
  </description>
